id: pm-fk84
title: "Least-privilege capability reconciliation: pm package doctor flags declared-but-unused extension capabilities + SDK assertExtensionCapabilityUsage"
description: "Add the inverse of the existing missing-capability enforcement (pm-mwwp): detect capabilities a package manifest DECLARES but never EXERCISES at activation, so authors can trim manifests to least privilege. Surfaced as advisory extension_capability_unused warnings in pm package/extension doctor, plus a batteries-included SDK test helper assertExtensionCapabilityUsage so authors catch over-declaration at npm test time. Closes the least-privilege loop opened by pm-bav0 (scaffold least-privilege metadata) and pm-mwwp (enforce missing capabilities)."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[6]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",capability,context-management,doctor,least-privilege
